comments: Lopez (MIL) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Crowder (MIL) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that Sasser's (DET) jump shot attempt makes contact with the rim and the shot clock is reset to 14 seconds.
Lopez (MIL) jumps from point A to point B and initiates contact to Cunningham's (DET) body, which affects his shot attempt in the lane.
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in Thompson's (DET) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Duren (DET) moves alongside Lillard's (MIL) path and marginal body contact occurs contesting his driving shot attempt.
Duren (DET) extends a hand into Lillard (MIL) during the pick and initiates contact that displaces him from his defensive position.
Duren (DET) is moving alongside Lillard's (MIL) path and marginal body contact occurs as the two come together during Lillard's drive.
Lopez (MIL) briefly grabs Stewart's (DET) arm as the two players engage and Lopez falls to the floor on his own after releasing.
Lillard (MIL) is moving alongside Cunningham's (DET) path and lightly brushes Cunningham's lower body as he gathers the ball at the of his drive.
Crowder (MIL) and Stewart (DET) engage and disengage with one another as they come together in pursuit of the loose ball.
Lopez (MIL) places a hand on Stewart's (DET) shoulder during his layup attempt, but the contact is marginal.
Duren (DET) extends an arm into Lopez's (MIL) head as he is returning to the floor during the loose ball situation.
Thompson (DET) reaches in and makes contact with the ball and Crowder (MIL) trips and falls over his own teammate.
Sasser (DET) places his hand to Lillard's (MIL) side and marginal contact occurs during Lillard's  drive to the basket.
Payne (MIL) establishes himself in Sasser's (DET) path and absorbs the contact.
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in Thompson's (DET) path and marginal contact occurs to his side as Thompson defends over the pick.
Lopez (MIL) cleanly blocks Cunningham's (DET) driving shot attempt before incidental contact occurs.

Stewart (DET) lightly brushes Beasley's (MIL) head as the steal occurs.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Thompson (DET) commits a take foul on Crowder (MIL).
Crowder (MIL) deflects the entry pass to Cunningham (DET) prior to incidental body contact occurring.
Cunningham (DET) establishes himself in Payne's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs to Payne's side as they disengage.
Duren (DET) establishes himself in Beasley's (MIL) path and is firming up when marginal contact occurs during the screen.
